1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:32,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,175 --> 00:00:40,645
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,645 --> 00:00:42,075
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:43,885 --> 00:00:45,555
I was just organizing some books.

5
00:00:45,955 --> 00:00:48,085
- Did you have lunch?
- A little while ago.

6
00:00:48,155 --> 00:00:50,155
- What about you?
- No.

7
00:00:50,485 --> 00:00:52,085
I should starve a little
to fit into my tuxedo.

8
00:00:53,155 --> 00:00:54,955
You're joking, right?

9
00:00:55,095 --> 00:00:56,325
A joke would be a waste of time.

10
00:00:56,595 --> 00:00:58,125
I saw Yong Joong yesterday
and suggested the four of us...

11
00:00:58,125 --> 00:00:59,265
get together for a meal.

12
00:01:02,135 --> 00:01:03,265
What did she say to you?

13
00:01:03,665 --> 00:01:04,735
Was she hurt?

14
00:01:05,035 --> 00:01:07,035
It's not as simple...

15
00:01:07,035 --> 00:01:08,105
as getting hurt or hurting someone.

16
00:01:08,175 --> 00:01:09,905
Stop beating around the bush.

17
00:01:11,475 --> 00:01:12,975
Get to the point with facts.

18
00:01:16,645 --> 00:01:17,645
The fact is,

19
00:01:18,515 --> 00:01:19,585
I'm staying out of it.

20
00:01:21,915 --> 00:01:23,285
We're still good, right?

21
00:01:33,995 --> 00:01:35,295
We didn't discuss anything in particular.

22
00:01:35,765 --> 00:01:36,935
I don't want to.

23
00:01:37,405 --> 00:01:38,535
Are you never going to see him again?

24
00:01:42,475 --> 00:01:43,845
(We're ready for the surgery.)

25
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:47,015
I'm not attending the wedding either.

26
00:01:47,145 --> 00:01:48,175
All right.

27
00:01:53,585 --> 00:01:55,955
She's an orphan, so you have to help her.

28
00:01:56,155 --> 00:01:58,185
Can't you hide Kim Jin Ju
in a hospital this big?

29
00:01:59,425 --> 00:02:01,725
And it'd be easy enough
to alter her appearance a bit.

30
00:02:20,575 --> 00:02:21,845
Two lattes, please.

31
00:02:35,295 --> 00:02:36,895
One Americano.

32
00:02:44,565 --> 00:02:45,565
Ready!

33
00:02:46,235 --> 00:02:47,235
Action!

34
00:02:52,715 --> 00:02:53,945
What do you think you're doing?

35
00:02:53,945 --> 00:02:55,075
We're over!

36
00:03:10,495 --> 00:03:11,525
Cut!

37
00:03:11,525 --> 00:03:12,735
What are you doing? Get in!

38
00:03:13,165 --> 00:03:14,565
Excuse me! Wait!

39
00:03:14,635 --> 00:03:15,705
Hey, Momo!

40
00:03:20,975 --> 00:03:23,475
(Nua General Hospital)

41
00:03:27,915 --> 00:03:28,945
Are you uncomfortable?

42
00:03:36,125 --> 00:03:38,385
Hey, take me to Nua General Hospital.

43
00:03:39,355 --> 00:03:41,325
Nua General Hospital?
Are you feeling unwell?

44
00:03:44,195 --> 00:03:48,135
(Nua General Hospital, Neurology Center)

45
00:04:20,465 --> 00:04:23,205
(Nua General Hospital)

46
00:04:48,155 --> 00:04:51,265
(Nua General Hospital)

47
00:05:14,315 --> 00:05:15,925
(Actress Momo)

48
00:05:15,985 --> 00:05:16,985
I'm done.

49
00:05:19,525 --> 00:05:21,295
(Nua General Hospital)

50
00:05:54,455 --> 00:05:56,725
Are you not in, Mr. Kim?

51
00:05:58,225 --> 00:06:00,935
I'll tell you more once I find my child.

52
00:06:01,365 --> 00:06:02,935
It was CEO Hyun Ran Hee all along.

53
00:06:03,505 --> 00:06:05,835
And they met again
because I bought a painting.

54
00:06:09,775 --> 00:06:13,675
I'd probably feel the same way about me
if I were you.

55
00:06:13,945 --> 00:06:14,945
Right?

56
00:06:16,115 --> 00:06:18,785
He's my brother,
but I raised him like my own son...

57
00:06:18,785 --> 00:06:19,915
and took care of him.

58
00:06:20,685 --> 00:06:22,355
So frankly, I'm a little disappointed.

59
00:06:23,285 --> 00:06:24,425
But what can I do?

60
00:06:26,195 --> 00:06:27,595
I'll treat Yong Joong well.

61
00:06:29,495 --> 00:06:31,395
I heard you had an older sister.

62
00:06:31,765 --> 00:06:35,035
Was Paul Kim, the artist,
CEO Hyun's first love?

63
00:06:37,005 --> 00:06:38,005
Yes.

64
00:06:38,735 --> 00:06:42,135
I met him a couple of times
after my mother passed away.

65
00:06:42,375 --> 00:06:44,245
He was desperately searching
for his lost daughter.

66
00:06:44,575 --> 00:06:45,575
How about you?

67
00:06:47,615 --> 00:06:48,975
I'm asking if you want to meet her.

68
00:06:50,885 --> 00:06:54,185
Of course. You know I grew up lonely.

69
00:06:54,885 --> 00:06:56,485
But I think it's going to be hard.

70
00:06:57,085 --> 00:06:59,725
The restaurant owner who brought the baby
from Japan to Korea...

71
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:01,995
could be raising the child herself.

72
00:07:02,965 --> 00:07:07,395
I hired a PI to look for Kim Jin Ju,
but he found a dead girl with that name.

73
00:07:13,575 --> 00:07:16,405
They say drinking cold stuff like that
can make it harder to get pregnant.

74
00:07:16,745 --> 00:07:18,405
That's what the director
at the Seonyeon Medical Clinic says.

75
00:07:19,275 --> 00:07:21,375
I might not let you see the baby
when it's born.

76
00:07:22,145 --> 00:07:23,945
You'd better treat me right.

77
00:07:37,065 --> 00:07:38,795
When are you having your bridal shower?

78
00:07:43,165 --> 00:07:44,165
I'm not having one.

79
00:07:45,635 --> 00:07:48,435
I brought this for you.
It's Pickles' replacement.

80
00:07:51,375 --> 00:07:52,405
No, thanks.

81
00:07:52,875 --> 00:07:57,415
Susan, Ah Ri, Jin Ju Kyung,
Ma Yeon Su, and Bo Ra.

82
00:07:57,745 --> 00:07:59,045
They all came.

83
00:08:02,115 --> 00:08:04,985
You have to throw one.
It's a once-in-a-lifetime thing...

84
00:08:06,555 --> 00:08:07,855
It'll only happen once, right?

85
00:08:09,725 --> 00:08:11,865
You've had too much to drink.
Go on and get some rest.

86
00:08:12,865 --> 00:08:15,495
I don't want to sober up.
I'm in such a good mood.

87
00:08:17,435 --> 00:08:18,465
I want to drink more.

88
00:08:19,305 --> 00:08:22,075
Let's go to a karaoke bar.
We've never gone together.

89
00:08:23,205 --> 00:08:26,075
We've been four times already,
including the last time.

90
00:08:26,915 --> 00:08:28,845
We won't see each other
after I get married, right?

91
00:08:32,015 --> 00:08:33,115
This is how we're saying goodbye?

92
00:08:33,585 --> 00:08:35,085
We should at least have a proper send-off.

93
00:08:36,985 --> 00:08:38,325
- Manager Oh.
- Yes?

94
00:08:38,385 --> 00:08:39,995
- The Silro Hotel.
- Okay.

95
00:08:40,055 --> 00:08:41,795
I came out without my wallet.

96
00:08:42,595 --> 00:08:43,795
You think I'd make you pay?

97
00:08:54,235 --> 00:08:57,875
Imagine how bleak the world would be
without flowers.

98
00:08:59,005 --> 00:09:01,575
She never really liked flowers
that much...

99
00:09:04,315 --> 00:09:06,655
My future brother-in-law, James.

100
00:09:08,555 --> 00:09:10,625
Do you know any women
you could set him up with?

101
00:09:10,955 --> 00:09:12,425
Even a divorced reporter would do.

102
00:09:14,095 --> 00:09:15,225
You don't want to answer?

103
00:09:16,195 --> 00:09:17,595
Just rest on the way.

104
00:09:17,595 --> 00:09:19,495
This is how I rest, by chatting.

105
00:09:21,895 --> 00:09:23,165
Is it just me?

106
00:09:23,305 --> 00:09:25,505
You look like you're looking down on me.

107
00:09:27,435 --> 00:09:29,205
Why would I look down on you, Momo?

108
00:09:29,205 --> 00:09:30,905
When you marry Ju Shin,

109
00:09:31,675 --> 00:09:33,645
are you going to start calling me
your sister-in-law?

110
00:09:39,145 --> 00:09:42,955
Honestly, you don't even like him.
You're just going through with it, right?

111
00:09:45,125 --> 00:09:46,125
I've grown to like him.

112
00:09:46,795 --> 00:09:49,125
What is there to like? Like what?

113
00:09:49,695 --> 00:09:50,825
He has his charms.

114
00:09:52,935 --> 00:09:55,195
And how long do you think
that charm will last?

115
00:09:55,965 --> 00:09:57,405
Happiness isn't easy.

116
00:09:58,235 --> 00:09:59,335
You have to work at it.

117
00:10:00,935 --> 00:10:02,635
You think I didn't try?

118
00:10:09,585 --> 00:10:10,585
Hello?

119
00:10:12,285 --> 00:10:13,385
Oh my, when?

120
00:10:14,715 --> 00:10:15,985
I didn't know.

121
00:10:15,985 --> 00:10:18,285
I'm Kim Jin Ju.

122
00:10:18,355 --> 00:10:19,825
Well, congratulations.

123
00:10:20,755 --> 00:10:21,755
Yes.

124
00:10:22,095 --> 00:10:23,365
I'll check my schedule.

125
00:10:24,395 --> 00:10:25,395
Okay.

126
00:10:36,275 --> 00:10:38,975
Your mom wouldn't let you get a cat
when you wanted one, remember?

127
00:10:39,275 --> 00:10:40,775
She hated how they shed.

128
00:10:40,845 --> 00:10:42,015
Was that it?

129
00:10:45,045 --> 00:10:46,755
Do you ever think about Kim Jin Ju?

130
00:10:51,385 --> 00:10:52,685
You don't? Not at all?

131
00:10:53,325 --> 00:10:54,695
How could I not?

132
00:10:55,995 --> 00:10:56,995
Why?

133
00:10:57,525 --> 00:10:59,065
She just pops into my head now and then.

134
00:11:00,935 --> 00:11:02,365
What do you think about?

135
00:11:02,495 --> 00:11:04,165
Good memories? Bad ones?

136
00:11:08,135 --> 00:11:10,645
Kim Jin Ju used to talk about you a lot.

137
00:11:11,445 --> 00:11:13,975
She said you both relied on each other
to get through your time at the orphanage.

138
00:11:22,285 --> 00:11:23,655
That heartless tramp.

139
00:11:24,155 --> 00:11:25,285
You said you wanted to sing, didn't you?

140
00:11:26,525 --> 00:11:27,525
Any requests?

141
00:11:28,055 --> 00:11:30,065
Just sing whatever you want.

142
00:11:30,065 --> 00:11:31,325
What did I sing last time?

143
00:11:32,935 --> 00:11:34,065
How would I know?

144
00:11:35,165 --> 00:11:36,235
You don't remember?

145
00:11:38,935 --> 00:11:41,205
Of course I do.
It's my go-to karaoke song.

146
00:11:44,075 --> 00:11:45,075
But today...

147
00:11:47,775 --> 00:11:49,545
(My Love is Far Away)

148
00:12:03,525 --> 00:12:08,335
I should have told you

149
00:12:10,365 --> 00:12:16,405
That I loved you

150
00:12:18,145 --> 00:12:23,115
That without you

151
00:12:24,985 --> 00:12:30,655
I can't live on

152
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:37,765
I should have told you

153
00:12:39,565 --> 00:12:45,305
That I loved you

154
00:12:47,335 --> 00:12:52,675
But I hesitated

155
00:12:54,575 --> 00:12:59,815
And my love is gone

156
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:06,295
I gave you my heart

157
00:13:10,325 --> 00:13:13,895
I gave you my tears

158
00:13:17,565 --> 00:13:21,705
And I gave you my dreams

159
00:13:24,175 --> 00:13:28,845
But you drifted away

160
00:13:30,545 --> 00:13:35,515
My love is far away

161
00:13:37,525 --> 00:13:42,695
Forever far away

162
00:13:45,195 --> 00:13:50,205
But I hesitated

163
00:13:52,335 --> 00:13:57,245
And my love is gone

164
00:14:17,925 --> 00:14:19,165
You try getting hit.

165
00:14:19,295 --> 00:14:20,835
You know what that's like,
the humiliation.

166
00:14:21,535 --> 00:14:22,765
I never said that.

167
00:14:24,135 --> 00:14:26,105
You did. Some time ago.

168
00:14:36,315 --> 00:14:37,315
Hey.

169
00:14:37,745 --> 00:14:40,215
- I guess I'm not that girly.
- Why?

170
00:14:40,215 --> 00:14:41,855
I just don't get the big deal
about flowers.

171
00:14:42,355 --> 00:14:43,385
Really?

172
00:14:43,825 --> 00:14:45,255
Maybe it's because I get them so often?

173
00:14:46,495 --> 00:14:48,955
No. I've just always been like that.

174
00:14:49,155 --> 00:14:50,795
They just don't do anything for me.

175
00:14:51,195 --> 00:14:53,795
(Jaeil Apartments)

176
00:14:54,835 --> 00:14:57,065
First floor. The doors are closing.

177
00:15:01,035 --> 00:15:02,805
Hey, you take the cat.

178
00:15:03,405 --> 00:15:04,405
Okay.

179
00:15:16,755 --> 00:15:17,755
(Director Shin Ju Shin)

180
00:15:25,225 --> 00:15:26,365
In the dead of night,

181
00:15:27,695 --> 00:15:29,265
you're not exactly dressed for a walk.

182
00:15:30,005 --> 00:15:31,235
I was coming to see you.

183
00:15:32,365 --> 00:15:33,535
What brings you here?

184
00:15:33,535 --> 00:15:34,705
There's something I need to talk about.

185
00:15:35,505 --> 00:15:36,745
Is there a good place to talk nearby?

186
00:15:38,145 --> 00:15:39,475
Why don't you come up for a minute?

187
00:15:41,915 --> 00:15:42,945
No.

188
00:15:43,515 --> 00:15:44,515
Some other time.

189
00:15:51,455 --> 00:15:52,525
Is something wrong?

190
00:15:55,025 --> 00:15:56,025
Momo.

191
00:15:57,425 --> 00:15:59,025
Haven't you noticed anything strange
about her?

192
00:16:03,065 --> 00:16:04,165
It seems like...

193
00:16:05,905 --> 00:16:07,035
she's possessed.

194
00:16:08,005 --> 00:16:09,235
I'm almost certain.

195
00:16:13,345 --> 00:16:15,715
- About that matter...
- So you've noticed it too?

196
00:16:18,145 --> 00:16:19,145
If...

197
00:16:21,415 --> 00:16:22,915
you could become Momo...

198
00:16:24,355 --> 00:16:25,585
without Yong Joong knowing...

199
00:16:29,225 --> 00:16:30,595
This might be your last chance...

200
00:16:31,665 --> 00:16:32,865
to become Momo...

201
00:16:33,465 --> 00:16:34,965
and marry Yong Joong.

202
00:16:39,505 --> 00:16:40,905
You're not the joking type.

203
00:16:41,435 --> 00:16:42,535
I'm not joking.

204
00:16:43,545 --> 00:16:45,175
I'm saying I can make it happen
if you want.

205
00:16:47,575 --> 00:16:48,575
There is a way.

206
00:16:53,185 --> 00:16:54,385
She's not possessed.

207
00:16:59,585 --> 00:17:00,795
It really is Kim Jin Ju.

208
00:17:07,265 --> 00:17:08,665
What do you mean?

209
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:13,005
How?

210
00:17:16,375 --> 00:17:17,445
A brain swap.

211
00:17:26,045 --> 00:17:28,615
She only looks like Momo. Just the body.

212
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:34,455
First, it was Momo's mom, CEO Hyun.

213
00:17:35,495 --> 00:17:36,525
And then Kim Jin Ju.

214
00:17:39,195 --> 00:17:40,435
It's hard to believe,

215
00:17:41,995 --> 00:17:43,135
but I'm the one who did the surgery.

216
00:17:43,535 --> 00:17:44,605
How can you...

217
00:17:47,405 --> 00:17:49,175
swap brains?

218
00:17:49,305 --> 00:17:52,975
Remember last time I said
I could be world-renowned if I wanted to?

219
00:17:54,315 --> 00:17:55,445
My late father,

220
00:17:57,645 --> 00:17:59,715
Momo's mom, Kim Jin Ju,

221
00:18:00,855 --> 00:18:02,785
Lee Shim, and Nurse Park Soo
are the only ones who know.

222
00:18:04,925 --> 00:18:05,925
Why?

223
00:18:07,525 --> 00:18:08,655
Momo's brain...

224
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:11,725
was too...

225
00:18:12,365 --> 00:18:13,495
damaged...

226
00:18:14,995 --> 00:18:16,335
from the diving accident back then.

227
00:18:19,365 --> 00:18:21,735
Momo's mom said it was the only way.

228
00:18:24,805 --> 00:18:26,615
I thought Jin Ju had really died,

229
00:18:28,775 --> 00:18:31,145
so I thought her spirit possessed Momo.

230
00:18:34,355 --> 00:18:36,785
Still, you'd have to be a fool
not to notice.

231
00:18:37,055 --> 00:18:40,695
Especially since even I, Kim Jin Ju,
have won over Ha Yong Joong.

232
00:18:40,755 --> 00:18:43,155
How are you going to live with yourself,
Geum Ba Ra?

233
00:18:54,735 --> 00:18:56,475
Life is worth living.

234
00:18:57,405 --> 00:18:59,475
Even when you're at rock bottom.

235
00:19:03,585 --> 00:19:05,245
Should I just come out and say
I'm Kim Jin Ju?

236
00:19:07,815 --> 00:19:09,355
If you want, I can swap your brain.

237
00:19:11,085 --> 00:19:12,225
Then what happens to Jin Ju?

238
00:19:18,095 --> 00:19:19,725
No, I don't want her taking over my body.

239
00:19:21,935 --> 00:19:22,935
I refuse.

240
00:19:24,835 --> 00:19:27,405
You should've let me see Momo once
before her surgery.

241
00:19:29,335 --> 00:19:30,575
You were better off not seeing her.

242
00:19:31,345 --> 00:19:32,605
Was it that bad?

243
00:19:38,615 --> 00:19:39,845
Anyway, think about it.

244
00:19:47,255 --> 00:19:49,025
Now that I think about it,
it's not me you're doing this for, is it?

245
00:19:53,025 --> 00:19:54,295
Just follow your heart.

246
00:19:55,295 --> 00:19:56,565
Your true feelings.

247
00:19:58,305 --> 00:19:59,635
It doesn't matter to me.

248
00:20:03,035 --> 00:20:05,005
Do all women look this beautiful
under the moonlight?

249
00:20:14,315 --> 00:20:15,885
Just like last time in my garden.

250
00:20:21,295 --> 00:20:22,295
To be honest...

251
00:20:24,325 --> 00:20:26,295
I only made that offer
hoping you'd say no.

252
00:20:28,565 --> 00:20:31,005
My conscience keeps nagging at me,

253
00:20:31,905 --> 00:20:33,235
but I just can't seem to ignore it.

254
00:20:37,705 --> 00:20:39,875
Didn't you say you've been holding on
because of Ha Yong Joong?

255
00:20:41,745 --> 00:20:42,845
To me, you...

256
00:20:44,945 --> 00:20:46,045
are not nearly that serious.

257
00:20:49,755 --> 00:20:50,755
Change...

258
00:20:55,425 --> 00:20:56,425
Okay?

259
00:21:09,735 --> 00:21:11,305
I guess the body is meaningless.

260
00:21:13,305 --> 00:21:15,445
She really wasn't the Momo I used to know.

261
00:21:17,585 --> 00:21:20,615
I guess everyone is born
with their own disposition.

262
00:21:22,715 --> 00:21:23,725
What about the baby?

263
00:21:25,885 --> 00:21:27,655
She got pregnant before Jin Ju's surgery.

264
00:21:30,795 --> 00:21:32,525
This is a little awkward.

265
00:21:35,135 --> 00:21:36,765
This is the last thing I can do for you.

266
00:21:37,835 --> 00:21:39,835
My feelings for you haven't changed.

267
00:21:40,675 --> 00:21:42,075
There was nothing to change
in the first place.

268
00:21:43,905 --> 00:21:45,175
We never even dated.

269
00:21:51,715 --> 00:21:52,785
What do you think of my name?

270
00:21:57,725 --> 00:21:58,725
I...

271
00:22:00,055 --> 00:22:01,555
don't like the "Shin" part of it.

272
00:22:03,725 --> 00:22:04,995
Although the characters are different,

273
00:22:05,365 --> 00:22:07,135
it keeps making me think
of the "Shin" for "ghost."

274
00:22:31,025 --> 00:22:32,785
I've succeeded both times,

275
00:22:33,855 --> 00:22:35,125
so don't you worry.

276
00:23:52,435 --> 00:23:55,875
Turns out it wasn't temporary kleptomania
she had during her period.

277
00:23:55,875 --> 00:23:56,975
It was out of habit.

278
00:23:56,975 --> 00:23:59,805
So how could
we keep living together as a family?

279
00:24:00,975 --> 00:24:03,475
It would cause problems
for him eventually.

280
00:24:04,845 --> 00:24:07,485
I'm so sorry that I can barely face you.

281
00:24:07,855 --> 00:24:09,155
I'm speechless.

282
00:24:09,685 --> 00:24:11,355
I'm just glad...

283
00:24:12,255 --> 00:24:15,095
- it's been cleared up now.
- Watch out for Jin Ju.

284
00:24:16,125 --> 00:24:18,925
If she has betrayed you once,
she's bound to do it again.

285
00:24:39,745 --> 00:24:40,755
Momo...

286
00:24:43,015 --> 00:24:44,025
It's so true.

287
00:24:45,785 --> 00:24:47,995
You would never do that to me.

288
00:24:54,135 --> 00:24:55,165
Congratulations!

289
00:25:00,135 --> 00:25:01,535
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

290
00:25:32,135 --> 00:25:33,365
Although we're not blood-related,

291
00:25:33,365 --> 00:25:36,435
my cousin in Germany was very sick,
so I went for a visit.

292
00:25:36,635 --> 00:25:38,175
I see.

293
00:25:38,645 --> 00:25:41,745
I was worried something was wrong,
so I dropped by your house in Yangpyeong.

294
00:25:44,585 --> 00:25:46,185
Say hello. This is the artist, Paul Kim.

295
00:25:46,685 --> 00:25:48,985
- This is Manager Yoon.
- It's a pleasure to meet you.

296
00:25:51,425 --> 00:25:53,895
Our CEO is a great admirer of your work.

297
00:26:10,205 --> 00:26:11,545
I heard from Momo...

298
00:26:12,205 --> 00:26:14,375
that the birth mother of the daughter
you're looking for is CEO Hyun.

299
00:26:17,245 --> 00:26:19,085
It's a small world, isn't it?

300
00:26:20,315 --> 00:26:21,855
Have you been invited to the wedding?

301
00:26:23,555 --> 00:26:25,985
- Not yet.
- We'd be happy to invite you.

302
00:26:27,125 --> 00:26:28,125
To be honest,

303
00:26:28,455 --> 00:26:30,895
since she was engaged
to Director Shin Ju Shin,

304
00:26:31,225 --> 00:26:32,895
it was a bit awkward from my end.

305
00:26:33,095 --> 00:26:35,565
I don't know how you'll take this, but...

306
00:26:36,495 --> 00:26:37,705
Don't worry about me.

307
00:26:40,165 --> 00:26:41,235
That's perfectly understandable.

308
00:26:43,375 --> 00:26:45,275
The officer in charge of the case
back then said...

309
00:26:45,975 --> 00:26:48,245
that the person on the CCTV
looked like a total pro.

310
00:26:48,845 --> 00:26:52,885
Thanks to this man,
Jin Ju barely avoided juvie.

311
00:26:54,755 --> 00:26:57,855
Jin Ju's been secretly reading your diary.

312
00:26:58,055 --> 00:26:59,285
She did it again last night.

313
00:27:00,285 --> 00:27:02,195
Promise you won't tell her
you heard it from me.

314
00:27:09,665 --> 00:27:10,705
You scared me.

315
00:27:16,275 --> 00:27:17,305
When did you get here?

316
00:27:20,715 --> 00:27:22,015
Let me go get changed.

317
00:27:28,785 --> 00:27:30,725
She's figured it out, hasn't she?

318
00:27:36,555 --> 00:27:37,825
Why are you staring at me like that?

319
00:27:41,465 --> 00:27:42,495
Are you Kim Jin Ju?

320
00:27:51,075 --> 00:27:52,775
Kim Gwang Cheol was right.

321
00:27:53,875 --> 00:27:55,515
He said you'd never take your life.

322
00:27:55,515 --> 00:27:56,945
What's your point?

323
00:27:57,345 --> 00:27:58,415
I'll pretend I don't know.

324
00:27:59,315 --> 00:28:00,585
But leave Yong Joong alone.

325
00:28:03,215 --> 00:28:04,385
You can easily find...

326
00:28:05,255 --> 00:28:06,955
someone so much better.

327
00:28:07,425 --> 00:28:08,455
No.

328
00:28:08,795 --> 00:28:10,455
I like Yong Joong too, you know.

329
00:28:10,765 --> 00:28:12,725
- A lot.
- Since when?

330
00:28:13,025 --> 00:28:15,065
- Even if the whole world is...
- If I tell him,

331
00:28:15,335 --> 00:28:16,865
will he still like you?

332
00:28:18,405 --> 00:28:21,335
It's the soul that matters, not the body.

333
00:28:22,205 --> 00:28:25,275
The brain is just a chunk of protein.

334
00:28:27,975 --> 00:28:31,485
Tell him. If he doesn't believe you,
I'll show him the surgical scar.

335
00:28:32,285 --> 00:28:33,285
Want to see it?

336
00:28:33,855 --> 00:28:34,855
Forget it.

337
00:28:35,455 --> 00:28:36,985
If I tell the whole world...

338
00:28:37,655 --> 00:28:40,485
that Director Shin Ju Shin of Nua Hospital
performed a brain swap...

339
00:28:41,495 --> 00:28:43,525
Even if there have been head transplants,

340
00:28:43,525 --> 00:28:45,325
wouldn't a brain-only transplant
be a world first?

341
00:28:49,035 --> 00:28:51,235
People would absolutely lose their minds.

342
00:28:54,205 --> 00:28:55,305
And then what happens?

343
00:28:56,375 --> 00:28:58,675
He'd get a few years for murder,
wouldn't he?

344
00:28:59,545 --> 00:29:01,475
CEO Hyun, Kim Jin Ju...

345
00:29:03,945 --> 00:29:06,785
Momo's mom has a place in a columbarium,
so we can just say she killed herself.

346
00:29:09,255 --> 00:29:10,415
But what about me? Kim Jin Ju?

347
00:29:12,625 --> 00:29:15,055
I don't even know
how they disposed of my body.

348
00:29:16,955 --> 00:29:18,165
I can't even ask them.

349
00:29:22,495 --> 00:29:23,765
Forget a grave,

350
00:29:24,365 --> 00:29:25,905
I vanished without a trace...

351
00:29:27,135 --> 00:29:28,175
from this world.

352
00:29:32,475 --> 00:29:35,245
You just can't stand to see me succeed,
can you?

353
00:29:37,015 --> 00:29:39,315
You should have just married
Director Shin.

354
00:29:40,315 --> 00:29:42,255
You loved him more than anyone.

355
00:29:42,315 --> 00:29:45,155
And you loved Ha Yong Joong
more than anyone.

356
00:29:47,495 --> 00:29:51,425
- After everything I've done for you...
- What about what I've done for you!

357
00:29:51,495 --> 00:29:53,465
- Should I spell it out for you?
- Go on!

358
00:29:56,295 --> 00:29:59,265
If I cross Attorney Tae Won Young,
he might retaliate.

359
00:29:59,705 --> 00:30:01,175
Not as a friend,

360
00:30:01,705 --> 00:30:03,975
I looked after you
like my own little sister.

361
00:30:06,475 --> 00:30:08,475
How can you say that so casually?

362
00:30:08,545 --> 00:30:10,615
I don't want to bring up that awful past.

363
00:30:10,745 --> 00:30:11,845
So, what's it going to be?

364
00:30:12,145 --> 00:30:13,915
Shall we go to the police station together
right now?

365
00:30:14,485 --> 00:30:16,655
Expose it all? To the whole world?

366
00:30:20,795 --> 00:30:24,465
I get why you like Yong Joong.

367
00:30:24,995 --> 00:30:26,825
He's just so, so sweet.

368
00:30:27,365 --> 00:30:29,195
He's completely different
from Director Shin.

369
00:30:31,005 --> 00:30:33,465
We're both starving for affection,
aren't we?

370
00:30:36,775 --> 00:30:39,505
All that pain
that's seared into our souls,

371
00:30:40,405 --> 00:30:41,915
a lot of it has already melted away.

372
00:30:48,255 --> 00:30:50,385
Just looking at Ha Yong Joong
makes me feel good,

373
00:30:51,485 --> 00:30:53,055
but you know that better than anyone.

374
00:30:58,895 --> 00:31:00,095
I feel so free.

375
00:31:00,865 --> 00:31:03,265
Now there's nothing left to hide,
is there?

376
00:31:03,895 --> 00:31:06,765
Secrets are surprisingly exhausting,
you know?

377
00:31:08,305 --> 00:31:10,405
We've both made it to the upper class now.

378
00:31:11,145 --> 00:31:14,515
You'll get to wear all the designer brands
you want now, right?

379
00:31:15,315 --> 00:31:18,145
As the wife of Nua Hospital's director
and its foundation.

380
00:31:19,245 --> 00:31:20,915
Aren't you afraid of divine judgment?

381
00:31:21,355 --> 00:31:23,715
Why would I? What's there to be afraid of?

382
00:31:23,885 --> 00:31:26,385
It's not like I was the one
who swapped our brains.

383
00:31:27,555 --> 00:31:30,455
The one who should be terrified
is Director Shin.

384
00:31:33,525 --> 00:31:34,935
What were you thinking,
spilling the beans?

385
00:31:34,935 --> 00:31:36,465
Did you confirm it with Director Shin?

386
00:31:40,505 --> 00:31:43,305
I admit, I was dying to tell someone.

387
00:31:44,675 --> 00:31:46,505
I was curious to see
how the world would react.

388
00:31:51,915 --> 00:31:53,615
You don't want to mess with me.

389
00:31:57,185 --> 00:31:58,925
And here I was, about to wish you well.

390
00:32:02,055 --> 00:32:03,225
Time to change my number.

391
00:32:11,735 --> 00:32:13,465
I hope I never have to see
your face again.

392
00:32:30,285 --> 00:32:33,855
Alright. Shoulder, 19 and a half.

393
00:32:51,675 --> 00:32:53,045
(Nua General Hospital)

394
00:32:59,015 --> 00:33:00,145
Are you not feeling well?

395
00:33:00,855 --> 00:33:01,915
No.

396
00:33:01,915 --> 00:33:02,985
Then,

397
00:33:03,585 --> 00:33:04,985
are you here to see Director Shin?

398
00:33:05,425 --> 00:33:06,955
I didn't get to see him.

399
00:33:08,195 --> 00:33:10,155
Let's have a cup of tea at the cafe here.

400
00:33:12,795 --> 00:33:15,565
I'm helping people park without pay.

401
00:33:23,305 --> 00:33:25,175
What's Director Shin like?

402
00:33:29,245 --> 00:33:31,615
Did he visit the orphanage
from time to time?

403
00:33:32,185 --> 00:33:33,515
Yes, a few times.

404
00:33:35,655 --> 00:33:36,855
Do you still...

405
00:33:38,425 --> 00:33:40,455
think that Jin Ju is still alive?

406
00:33:40,895 --> 00:33:42,325
Of course, I do.

407
00:33:42,755 --> 00:33:45,825
You're a reporter,
so think about it logically.

408
00:33:45,925 --> 00:33:47,865
If she really intended to kill herself,

409
00:33:47,995 --> 00:33:51,135
she would've jumped in the water
right in front of a CCTV camera.

410
00:33:52,435 --> 00:33:55,505
To make a big show of it
for the whole world to see.

411
00:33:59,145 --> 00:34:01,775
How long does she think
she can stay hidden?

412
00:34:04,915 --> 00:34:07,415
Have any relatives come looking
for you yet?

413
00:34:08,685 --> 00:34:09,855
No.

414
00:34:09,855 --> 00:34:12,925
I bet a shaman could tell us.

415
00:34:13,155 --> 00:34:16,095
But we don't know your date of birth,
so it's no use.

416
00:34:16,725 --> 00:34:19,525
Wasn't there some kind of note?
With your birth date and time on it.

417
00:34:22,235 --> 00:34:23,635
This is just hypothetical,

418
00:34:26,635 --> 00:34:29,835
- but if Jin Ju were really alive...
- Tell me what you know!

419
00:34:30,075 --> 00:34:31,545
- I don't...
- You know something!

420
00:34:31,845 --> 00:34:32,845
It's just that...

421
00:34:33,775 --> 00:34:36,045
I'm just curious why you can't seem
to give up on her.

422
00:34:36,545 --> 00:34:38,145
How could I give up on my own child?

423
00:34:38,485 --> 00:34:40,545
That's just how a parent's love is.

424
00:34:41,285 --> 00:34:43,685
But since I'm such a pathetic father...

425
00:34:45,125 --> 00:34:47,185
Imagine if I'd shown up as a rich dad.

426
00:34:48,695 --> 00:34:51,125
Do you think she would've just vanished
like she was dead?

427
00:34:51,995 --> 00:34:54,465
If you know anything at all,
please let me know.

428
00:34:55,895 --> 00:35:00,405
I'm sure of it.
Momo or Director Shin is hiding her.

429
00:35:02,905 --> 00:35:04,475
Why would Director Shin...

430
00:35:04,875 --> 00:35:07,715
He's extremely busy.
He wouldn't have time or energy for that.

431
00:35:07,775 --> 00:35:10,275
Because she came from his orphanage.

432
00:35:39,005 --> 00:35:42,145
The phone is turned off.
Please leave a message after the tone.

433
00:35:43,575 --> 00:35:45,445
Chairman Shin sits at the head table.

434
00:35:47,115 --> 00:35:48,555
And Yoon Su Hyun can sit wherever.

435
00:35:50,685 --> 00:35:52,125
Geum Ba Ra isn't coming.

436
00:35:53,585 --> 00:35:55,125
Do I have to explain everything?

437
00:36:02,335 --> 00:36:03,465
(Geum Ba Ra)

438
00:36:03,535 --> 00:36:06,035
(I enjoyed dinner. Thank...)

439
00:36:08,975 --> 00:36:12,845
(Dinner was delicious...)

440
00:36:16,575 --> 00:36:19,145
- Hello, Mr. Kim.
- Hello.

441
00:36:19,215 --> 00:36:20,985
Are you driving tomorrow?

442
00:36:22,115 --> 00:36:24,085
- To the wedding hall?
- Yes.

443
00:36:24,155 --> 00:36:26,025
I didn't get an invitation.

444
00:36:26,525 --> 00:36:27,525
Really?

445
00:36:27,525 --> 00:36:30,455
I understand. The press will be there,

446
00:36:30,525 --> 00:36:33,065
and it could start rumors
if we're not careful.

447
00:36:33,195 --> 00:36:35,895
Come on, we didn't say anything.
What kind of rumors?

448
00:36:36,035 --> 00:36:38,265
I was even wondering if you'd be walking
the bride down the aisle.

449
00:36:49,175 --> 00:36:50,415
(Geum Ba Ra)

450
00:37:03,255 --> 00:37:04,725
The number you have dialed...

451
00:37:04,725 --> 00:37:09,195
has been temporarily suspended
at the customer’s request.

452
00:37:20,345 --> 00:37:22,215
- Where's Momo?
- The restroom.

453
00:37:23,175 --> 00:37:25,215
- You're here.
- Did you sleep well?

454
00:37:25,215 --> 00:37:26,245
Yes.

455
00:37:26,885 --> 00:37:29,115
James, you should get a little
makeup done too.

456
00:37:29,285 --> 00:37:31,785
If I wear makeup, I'll outshine the groom.

457
00:37:33,055 --> 00:37:35,425
- Sir, some coffee...
- I already had some, thanks.

458
00:37:36,255 --> 00:37:38,295
Is Reporter Geum at my table?

459
00:37:38,925 --> 00:37:40,065
I don't know.

460
00:37:41,065 --> 00:37:42,235
She's probably not coming.

461
00:37:42,665 --> 00:37:44,635
Why isn't she coming? Of all people.

462
00:37:45,535 --> 00:37:47,535
I guess she felt awkward coming alone.

463
00:37:48,505 --> 00:37:50,705
I heard Paul wasn't invited either.

464
00:37:50,905 --> 00:37:52,945
Our guest list was just too long.

465
00:37:53,405 --> 00:37:55,245
So you're walking in alone?

466
00:37:56,545 --> 00:37:57,575
Together.

467
00:37:59,985 --> 00:38:04,825
We will shortly begin the wedding ceremony
for Ha Yong Joong and Momo.

468
00:38:04,885 --> 00:38:07,225
Would our guests please
make their way inside...

469
00:38:07,285 --> 00:38:09,925
and take their seats? Thank you.

470
00:38:09,995 --> 00:38:11,665
(It looks like no one's home.)

471
00:38:11,725 --> 00:38:14,465
The bride and groom will now
make their entrance together.

472
00:38:14,595 --> 00:38:17,095
Please give them a warm round of applause!

473
00:38:46,225 --> 00:38:47,265
Thank you.

474
00:40:15,585 --> 00:40:17,255
You know how in foreign movies,

475
00:40:17,555 --> 00:40:20,425
brides do a father-daughter dance
at the wedding.

476
00:40:21,155 --> 00:40:24,355
But no matter how many times I marry,
I won't have a dad to dance with.

477
00:40:25,665 --> 00:40:27,395
But I still wanted to learn how.

478
00:41:27,995 --> 00:41:28,995
Are you nervous?

479
00:41:29,555 --> 00:41:32,095
- No.
- Let's be less formal.

480
00:41:32,365 --> 00:41:33,625
We're married now.

481
00:42:08,295 --> 00:42:09,995
What's taking him so long?

482
00:42:12,535 --> 00:42:16,005
Every time I hear this music,
I always think...

483
00:42:18,205 --> 00:42:19,205
About me?

484
00:42:21,875 --> 00:42:24,415
What? Is there a story behind this song?

485
00:42:27,415 --> 00:42:29,415
My memory is really spotty.

486
00:42:29,555 --> 00:42:31,785
I just can't remember parts of things...

487
00:42:32,155 --> 00:42:34,085
that happened with people.

488
00:42:36,755 --> 00:42:38,265
It doesn't matter if you've forgotten.

489
00:42:46,005 --> 00:42:48,635
Are you bummed that Ba Ra
didn't come today?

490
00:42:55,345 --> 00:42:56,345
Call her.

491
00:42:56,845 --> 00:42:58,885
This should get under Ba Ra's skin.

492
00:43:01,815 --> 00:43:02,855
A video call.

493
00:43:12,095 --> 00:43:13,095
Are you tired?

494
00:43:13,425 --> 00:43:14,525
Are you?

495
00:43:17,995 --> 00:43:19,065
Let's be honest.

496
00:43:19,735 --> 00:43:21,405
We postponed our trip...

497
00:43:22,035 --> 00:43:24,675
for Ba Ra's wedding
and not because of work, right?

498
00:43:26,045 --> 00:43:28,005
If we're going to go,
we should plan it right.

499
00:43:28,545 --> 00:43:31,045
That way, we can make the most of our trip
since we rarely get to go.

500
00:43:31,175 --> 00:43:33,715
Wouldn't we be doing each other a favor
by not attending each other's weddings?

501
00:43:35,155 --> 00:43:37,755
It's meaningless unless
you're genuinely happy for them, right?

502
00:43:38,555 --> 00:43:41,455
James will go to represent
our family anyway.

503
00:43:42,695 --> 00:43:43,695
We'll see.

504
00:43:46,295 --> 00:43:47,325
I'm going to go wash up.

505
00:44:47,625 --> 00:44:49,055
The number you have dialed...

506
00:44:49,055 --> 00:44:51,295
has been temporarily suspended
at the customer's request.

507
00:45:19,055 --> 00:45:22,825
It was great,
but I feel like something was missing.

508
00:45:23,725 --> 00:45:24,725
What was it?

509
00:45:26,495 --> 00:45:28,665
I wonder how Ba Ra is feeling right now.

510
00:45:48,115 --> 00:45:50,715
(This is Geum Ba Ra. Director Shin,
I'm writing this with a heavy heart.)

511
00:45:53,125 --> 00:45:54,255
This is Geum Ba Ra.

512
00:45:55,425 --> 00:45:56,425
Director Shin,

513
00:45:57,325 --> 00:45:59,925
I'm writing this with a heavy heart.

514
00:46:01,225 --> 00:46:04,265
Due to my insecurities and shortcomings,
I couldn't face you in person,

515
00:46:05,005 --> 00:46:07,565
so please forgive me for saying
goodbye this way.

516
00:46:08,405 --> 00:46:12,675
In every way, I fall short
and am not worthy of you.

517
00:46:13,275 --> 00:46:17,715
I truly hope you meet someone wonderful
who is worthy of you,

518
00:46:17,975 --> 00:46:20,085
build a beautiful family,
and find happiness.

519
00:46:20,385 --> 00:46:22,655
I'll be praying for you with all my heart
from afar.

520
00:46:24,385 --> 00:46:27,185
I will never forget your kindness
and all you've done for me...

521
00:46:27,855 --> 00:46:29,655
for as long as I live,

522
00:46:30,195 --> 00:46:32,295
and I promise to repay you someday.

523
00:46:32,995 --> 00:46:35,395
Please take care of yourself and be well.

524
00:46:36,865 --> 00:46:37,865
Geum Ba Ra.

525
00:47:04,355 --> 00:47:07,295
I'll be honest, I'm not much of a cook.
I'll learn as I go.

526
00:47:07,695 --> 00:47:08,995
I barely eat breakfast anyway.

527
00:47:09,465 --> 00:47:11,195
Just some milk or coffee after my run.

528
00:47:11,565 --> 00:47:13,565
Besides, the meal kits these days
are so good.

529
00:47:14,205 --> 00:47:15,675
James will keep sending us side dishes.

530
00:47:15,675 --> 00:47:16,705
(James)

531
00:47:17,835 --> 00:47:18,845
Telepathy.

532
00:47:21,005 --> 00:47:23,415
- Hey, James.
- Where did Reporter Geum take off to now?

533
00:47:25,345 --> 00:47:28,045
- Why?
- She missed the wedding yesterday,

534
00:47:28,785 --> 00:47:31,655
so I got worried and texted her
to have lunch,

535
00:47:31,655 --> 00:47:32,755
but she hasn't replied.

536
00:47:32,955 --> 00:47:34,225
My texts aren't even going through.

537
00:47:34,485 --> 00:47:37,955
I called, and it says her line
has been suspended at her request.

538
00:47:42,165 --> 00:47:43,435
You haven't heard anything?

539
00:47:44,135 --> 00:47:45,405
I'll ask Ju Shin.

540
00:47:46,565 --> 00:47:47,565
Okay.

541
00:47:56,645 --> 00:47:58,645
- Hello?
- James says...

542
00:47:58,645 --> 00:48:00,115
Ba Ra's phone has been suspended.

543
00:48:00,945 --> 00:48:01,955
I know.

544
00:48:02,355 --> 00:48:04,385
Did she just take off on a trip by herself
right before the wedding?

545
00:48:06,255 --> 00:48:07,255
No.

546
00:48:08,455 --> 00:48:09,455
Did you two fight?

547
00:48:13,365 --> 00:48:14,365
Why?

548
00:48:19,335 --> 00:48:20,335
She's gone.

549
00:48:23,405 --> 00:48:25,305
- Where to?
- I don't know.

550
00:48:27,975 --> 00:48:28,975
She just disappeared.

551
00:48:30,575 --> 00:48:31,745
What do you mean, disappeared?

552
00:48:32,915 --> 00:48:34,415
- I'm hanging up.
- Wait.

553
00:48:48,495 --> 00:48:49,495
What did the email say?

554
00:48:54,205 --> 00:48:55,775
(This is Geum Ba Ra. Director Shin,
I'm writing this with a heavy heart.)

555
00:49:05,885 --> 00:49:08,185
She would never give up
on marrying Director Shin.

556
00:49:09,355 --> 00:49:11,055
She must have some other plan.

557
00:49:21,935 --> 00:49:23,165
It's not what you're thinking...

558
00:49:25,535 --> 00:49:26,965
Nothing happened between Ba Ra and me.

559
00:49:29,675 --> 00:49:33,145
She stayed at my place for a few days,
in the guest room.

560
00:49:36,875 --> 00:49:38,145
If I'd known it would turn out like this,

561
00:49:39,415 --> 00:49:42,315
I wonder if I should've just left things
as they were.

562
00:49:45,625 --> 00:49:46,625
What does Momo say?

563
00:49:48,525 --> 00:49:49,925
She said she'd turn up eventually,

564
00:49:50,995 --> 00:49:52,195
like last time.

565
00:49:58,135 --> 00:49:59,565
You were everything...

566
00:50:00,735 --> 00:50:01,735
to Ba Ra.

567
00:50:06,045 --> 00:50:08,515
She told me you were her everything.

568
00:50:11,115 --> 00:50:12,145
Why are you telling me this now?

569
00:50:13,315 --> 00:50:14,315
You seriously didn't know?

570
00:50:18,955 --> 00:50:20,355
You're not that dense.

571
00:50:21,485 --> 00:50:22,655
You even spent the night with her.

572
00:50:26,365 --> 00:50:28,195
You think Director Shin will find her?

573
00:50:28,495 --> 00:50:30,335
- If he really wanted to...
- He's looking into it.

574
00:50:31,095 --> 00:50:33,735
- You can't check immigration, right?
- Right.

575
00:50:34,465 --> 00:50:36,135
That's Reporter Geum for you, though.

576
00:50:37,105 --> 00:50:38,975
- What is?
- Her pride.

577
00:50:40,005 --> 00:50:42,975
Honestly, Ju Shin's love was one-sided.
Reporter Geum was just playing along.

578
00:50:43,975 --> 00:50:47,045
She grew up in that orphanage,
so she probably agreed out of obligation,

579
00:50:47,315 --> 00:50:48,615
but then realized she couldn't
go through with it.

580
00:50:48,955 --> 00:50:50,055
A loveless marriage.

581
00:50:51,955 --> 00:50:53,725
I bet she really went to Boston this time.

582
00:51:11,605 --> 00:51:13,645
She just couldn't take it anymore.

583
00:51:14,075 --> 00:51:16,745
She's been pining for Ha Yong Joong
for almost 20 years.

584
00:51:27,255 --> 00:51:29,125
Is there anything
Yong Joong particularly likes?

585
00:51:29,125 --> 00:51:30,755
He's not a picky eater.

586
00:51:32,065 --> 00:51:33,065
But still.

587
00:51:33,325 --> 00:51:35,535
Grilled fish.
He prefers it over soups or stews.

588
00:51:36,635 --> 00:51:38,135
But grilling fish makes
the whole place smell.

589
00:51:41,665 --> 00:51:43,905
Did Reporter Geum come over often?

590
00:51:44,635 --> 00:51:46,645
I don't think so. Not while I was here.

591
00:51:48,915 --> 00:51:49,915
What are you making?

592
00:51:50,315 --> 00:51:51,315
Vietnamese spring rolls.

593
00:51:51,315 --> 00:51:52,385
Forget that.

594
00:51:52,385 --> 00:51:54,685
You know, that dish where you stuff
minced meat and pan-fry it?

595
00:51:55,085 --> 00:51:58,115
- Make that instead.
- Stuff the meat into what?

596
00:51:58,555 --> 00:51:59,555
Bell peppers.

597
00:52:01,485 --> 00:52:02,825
But I've already prepped
everything for this.

598
00:52:03,995 --> 00:52:04,995
Take it home and eat it.

599
00:52:05,595 --> 00:52:06,595
How many people are in your family?

600
00:52:06,925 --> 00:52:07,925
Three of us.

601
00:52:08,695 --> 00:52:09,765
Are they girls or boys?

602
00:52:10,635 --> 00:52:11,635
Two daughters.

603
00:52:13,265 --> 00:52:14,265
Are you divorced?

604
00:52:15,165 --> 00:52:16,235
I'm a widow.

605
00:52:27,315 --> 00:52:28,785
You're a monster, Director Shin.

606
00:52:30,515 --> 00:52:32,125
You don't get to mess with my head.

607
00:52:46,865 --> 00:52:48,675
Did you leave because I'm that scary
and horrible to you?

608
00:52:56,775 --> 00:52:57,815
She's quite the princess.

609
00:53:03,885 --> 00:53:04,885
My goodness.

610
00:53:05,655 --> 00:53:08,585
It's a boy.
He finally decided to show us today.

611
00:53:12,025 --> 00:53:13,025
Right here.

612
00:53:25,305 --> 00:53:26,845
You don't want to mess with me.

613
00:53:28,345 --> 00:53:30,045
And here I was, about to wish you well.

614
00:54:02,575 --> 00:54:05,115
(Wongyeong Pharmacy)

615
00:54:09,215 --> 00:54:10,455
Yes, that'll be nine dollars.

616
00:54:10,515 --> 00:54:12,155
(Pregnancy test)

617
00:54:13,655 --> 00:54:15,825
I'll take one more, a different brand.

618
00:54:27,165 --> 00:54:29,305
(Pregnancy test)

619
00:54:33,975 --> 00:54:36,345
You're pregnant. You're five weeks along.

620
00:55:06,005 --> 00:55:09,445
(Yong Joong)

621
00:55:10,915 --> 00:55:12,815
(Yong Joong)

622
00:55:23,095 --> 00:55:24,095
What's up?

623
00:55:26,625 --> 00:55:27,895
Are you meeting someone here?

624
00:55:31,765 --> 00:55:32,935
No, I was just around.

625
00:55:35,805 --> 00:55:36,805
What about you?

626
00:55:37,905 --> 00:55:39,505
I was just heading out for a walk,

627
00:55:40,675 --> 00:55:41,675
and there you were.

628
00:55:45,985 --> 00:55:47,515
Didn't you work out this morning?

629
00:55:48,955 --> 00:55:50,915
- No.
- Then go do it.

630
00:55:53,225 --> 00:55:54,225
Have you had lunch?

631
00:55:55,055 --> 00:55:57,325
- Not yet.
- It's after two. Why not?

632
00:55:59,465 --> 00:56:01,795
- What about you?
- I haven't eaten either.

633
00:56:02,365 --> 00:56:03,835
I had an early meeting.

634
00:56:05,765 --> 00:56:07,605
You said this place
has good cold noodles, right?

635
00:56:09,335 --> 00:56:10,335
Let's go.

636
00:56:22,215 --> 00:56:23,215
Cold noodles with broth?

637
00:56:23,515 --> 00:56:24,515
Spicy noodles.

638
00:56:29,095 --> 00:56:31,025
- One broth, one spicy cold noodles.
- Okay.

639
00:56:31,995 --> 00:56:33,795
But you like spicy cold noodles too.

640
00:56:35,465 --> 00:56:36,735
So you can have mine
if yours is too spicy.

641
00:56:37,065 --> 00:56:38,665
Last time, you said it was a little spicy.

642
00:56:40,605 --> 00:56:42,335
I can just take some of the sauce out.

643
00:56:50,415 --> 00:56:51,445
How are you feeling?

644
00:56:52,945 --> 00:56:53,945
I'm fine.

645
00:56:55,985 --> 00:56:57,485
You look a little pale.

646
00:57:04,095 --> 00:57:05,255
How are the wedding plans going?

647
00:57:06,125 --> 00:57:08,265
Fine. There isn't much to do.

648
00:57:09,665 --> 00:57:10,695
I heard from my brother.

649
00:57:11,295 --> 00:57:12,465
You went for your dress fitting.

650
00:57:18,835 --> 00:57:21,675
Okay, just a natural,
conversational vibe, please.

651
00:58:08,125 --> 00:58:10,195
They're always so quick
at cold noodle places.

652
00:58:10,455 --> 00:58:12,565
The popular places
are constantly boiling noodles.

653
00:58:41,085 --> 00:58:42,085
Vinegar.

654
00:58:57,775 --> 00:58:59,875
I just don't get the appeal
of Pyeongyang-style cold noodles.

655
00:59:00,675 --> 00:59:03,445
My boss is a total Pyeongyang-style
cold noodles fanatic, though.

656
00:59:04,615 --> 00:59:05,885
Are you going back to work next year?

657
00:59:07,715 --> 00:59:08,715
No.

658
00:59:09,485 --> 00:59:11,215
Ju Shin doesn't want you to work, does he?

659
00:59:23,595 --> 00:59:24,595
Are you happy?

660
00:59:29,135 --> 00:59:30,335
It was your dream...

661
00:59:31,305 --> 00:59:32,775
to be with Momo,
whom you were so crazy about.

662
00:59:33,475 --> 00:59:34,975
I wouldn't call it a dream.

663
00:59:37,545 --> 00:59:39,685
She's not the same Momo you used to love.

664
00:59:47,585 --> 00:59:48,585
Is it too spicy for you?

665
00:59:49,095 --> 00:59:50,095
Is it okay?

666
00:59:57,165 --> 01:00:00,305
(Bukhyang Noodle House)

667
01:00:05,305 --> 01:00:06,305
Hey.

668
01:00:09,415 --> 01:00:10,575
By the way,

669
01:00:10,975 --> 01:00:12,275
you know...

670
01:00:16,715 --> 01:00:18,715
What kind of gift would you want from me?

671
01:00:19,155 --> 01:00:20,225
If you were to get one.

672
01:00:21,525 --> 01:00:22,595
A wedding gift?

673
01:00:25,295 --> 01:00:26,425
I should be the one getting you a gift.

674
01:00:27,495 --> 01:00:28,825
There's nothing I really need.

675
01:00:32,035 --> 01:00:33,035
Me neither.

676
01:00:43,475 --> 01:00:44,545
I'm glad...

677
01:00:46,085 --> 01:00:48,045
- you are enjoying it.
- It's delicious.

678
01:00:58,955 --> 01:00:59,965
Momo?

679
01:01:00,565 --> 01:01:01,565
No.

680
01:01:02,125 --> 01:01:03,195
The head of marketing.

681
01:01:03,265 --> 01:01:04,535
(Looks like only Tuesday
works for next week.)

682
01:01:21,145 --> 01:01:22,145
What's wrong?

683
01:01:22,685 --> 01:01:23,685
It's spicy.

684
01:01:24,715 --> 01:01:25,715
You should stop then.

685
01:01:26,455 --> 01:01:27,525
No, I'm okay.

686
01:01:27,985 --> 01:01:28,985
Here, have mine.

687
01:01:51,245 --> 01:01:52,945
Is there a convenience store around here?

688
01:01:54,015 --> 01:01:55,145
There's one over there.

689
01:01:56,455 --> 01:01:57,855
I want an ice-cream bar.

690
01:01:58,555 --> 01:02:01,555
Wouldn't a drink be better for spicy food?

691
01:02:02,755 --> 01:02:03,755
Ice cream.

692
01:02:21,675 --> 01:02:23,915
- I'll get the ice cream.
- Just buy me something expensive later.

693
01:02:29,315 --> 01:02:30,315
Okay.

694
01:02:39,725 --> 01:02:41,365
I guess you and Ju Shin
don't keep secrets from each other.

695
01:02:42,935 --> 01:02:44,395
He seemed to know all about us.

696
01:02:49,105 --> 01:02:50,105
Does that bother you?

697
01:02:51,305 --> 01:02:52,305
No.

698
01:02:53,205 --> 01:02:55,075
We never used to keep secrets
from each other.

699
01:03:04,785 --> 01:03:07,725
I realized that I didn't
really know Ju Shin completely...

700
01:03:10,155 --> 01:03:11,295
after I heard about the wedding.

701
01:03:19,405 --> 01:03:20,405
Anyway...

702
01:03:24,075 --> 01:03:26,645
Call me if you need anything.
Or if you want to talk something over.

703
01:03:30,515 --> 01:03:31,575
You know, in life,

704
01:03:32,785 --> 01:03:34,245
unexpected things can happen.

705
01:03:37,655 --> 01:03:38,655
Right?

706
01:03:40,285 --> 01:03:41,625
Momo wouldn't like that.

707
01:03:45,965 --> 01:03:47,325
What's between us
has nothing to do with Momo.

708
01:03:58,805 --> 01:03:59,805
What if...

709
01:04:01,405 --> 01:04:02,605
This is just a hypothetical, but...

710
01:04:07,545 --> 01:04:08,545
Never mind.

711
01:04:10,155 --> 01:04:11,155
Go ahead.

712
01:04:13,485 --> 01:04:14,825
It was great eating with you today.

713
01:04:16,525 --> 01:04:17,655
I was starving.

714
01:04:20,525 --> 01:04:22,695
I was really craving cold noodles.

715
01:04:23,295 --> 01:04:24,635
The kind you treat me to.

716
01:04:27,305 --> 01:04:28,935
You're already so skinny.
Don't go around skipping meals.

717
01:04:30,605 --> 01:04:31,975
Are you sure you don't want
anything to drink?

718
01:04:36,115 --> 01:04:37,275
I don't want to part ways.

719
01:04:38,245 --> 01:04:39,715
I want to stay with you a little longer.

720
01:04:42,145 --> 01:04:43,155
I'm too full.

721
01:04:48,185 --> 01:04:49,595
No, I'll throw it away.

722
01:05:12,945 --> 01:05:14,045
It's dried up.

723
01:05:26,695 --> 01:05:27,765
Take good care of yourself...

724
01:05:29,265 --> 01:05:30,265
so I don't worry.

725
01:05:31,695 --> 01:05:33,065
It's not that I don't want
to worry about you.

726
01:05:38,835 --> 01:05:39,905
You too.

727
01:05:43,675 --> 01:05:44,675
What were you going to say before?

728
01:05:46,885 --> 01:05:48,615
I forgot.

729
01:05:52,515 --> 01:05:53,525
Some other time.

730
01:05:56,295 --> 01:05:57,295
The truth is...

731
01:05:58,625 --> 01:05:59,865
I went to the cafe...

732
01:06:00,965 --> 01:06:02,025
hoping I might run into you.

733
01:06:06,105 --> 01:06:07,605
Wait here, I'll go get the car.

734
01:06:09,335 --> 01:06:10,635
No, if you're going to walk,
I'll walk with you.

735
01:06:10,905 --> 01:06:11,905
I'll wait here.

736
01:07:23,015 --> 01:07:24,975
The phone is turned off.

737
01:07:24,975 --> 01:07:27,985
Please leave a message after the tone.

738
01:07:28,245 --> 01:07:29,285
Charges will apply...

739
01:07:29,285 --> 01:07:30,555
(Ba Ra)

740
01:07:42,025 --> 01:07:44,835
Microwave the rockfish soup
for two minutes.

741
01:09:28,235 --> 01:09:29,235
Honey.

742
01:09:29,775 --> 01:09:31,975
We should've picked a cuter nickname
for the baby.

743
01:09:33,145 --> 01:09:34,445
It's plenty cute.

744
01:09:34,775 --> 01:09:37,015
I just don't think it suits a girl.

745
01:09:37,675 --> 01:09:38,775
What's wrong with Wani?

746
01:09:39,375 --> 01:09:40,385
It sounds like "You're here?"

747
01:09:44,215 --> 01:09:46,525
Don't tell me you're disappointed,
hoping for a boy.

748
01:09:48,685 --> 01:09:50,795
- They bought the expensive one.
- I'll add more...

749
01:09:50,855 --> 01:09:52,495
- Oh, this one?
- Yes.

750
01:09:53,825 --> 01:09:54,825
Here you go.

751
01:10:00,105 --> 01:10:01,105
Puffed rice!

752
01:10:04,505 --> 01:10:07,475
Tangerines, a basket for ten dollars!
Apples, a basket for ten dollars.

753
01:10:07,545 --> 01:10:09,145
Sir, would you like to try an apple?

754
01:10:10,615 --> 01:10:12,275
- How much are they?
- Ten dollars a basket.

755
01:10:12,345 --> 01:10:14,245
- Ten dollars?
- Yes.

756
01:10:14,315 --> 01:10:15,815
(Honey Apples, Ten dollars)

757
01:10:37,905 --> 01:10:38,975
Excuse me!

758
01:10:39,305 --> 01:10:41,405
I'll take one of these hairtails, please.

759
01:11:15,045 --> 01:11:16,175
If there are any spirits listening,

760
01:11:20,285 --> 01:11:21,685
please help me find my child.

761
01:11:27,225 --> 01:11:28,225
Please.

762
01:11:29,825 --> 01:11:33,565
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

763
01:11:36,025 --> 01:11:38,165
- I see you called.
- Did you find anything in Boston?

764
01:11:38,465 --> 01:11:40,105
I managed to track down the nun,

765
01:11:40,865 --> 01:11:42,205
but she said she hasn't heard a thing
from Ba Ra.

766
01:11:43,305 --> 01:11:45,135
Do you think Ba Ra told her to say that?

767
01:11:46,845 --> 01:11:47,845
No.

768
01:11:50,745 --> 01:11:52,175
So we're really out of options?

769
01:12:27,485 --> 01:12:30,755
Goodness, Mr. Kim. Hello.

770
01:12:31,115 --> 01:12:32,115
What brings you here?

771
01:13:06,185 --> 01:13:09,125
(Doctor Shin)

772
01:13:09,225 --> 01:13:10,655
When are you due?

773
01:13:11,055 --> 01:13:12,595
Are you about six months along?

774
01:13:12,695 --> 01:13:14,865
- The 12th of next month.
- Momo.

775
01:13:15,565 --> 01:13:18,095
She's getting what she deserves.

776
01:13:18,695 --> 01:13:20,605
- I'm taking a picture.
- Oh my gosh!

777
01:13:20,765 --> 01:13:24,705
Park Sun Woo said she just saw
Reporter Geum at a rest stop.

778
01:13:24,775 --> 01:13:26,575
- Reporter Geum Ba Ra?
- But...

779
01:13:26,575 --> 01:13:28,475
- But what?
- She said she looked different.

780
01:13:28,475 --> 01:13:29,545
Looked different?

781
01:13:29,605 --> 01:13:31,415
Hyun Ran Hee visited today.

782
01:13:31,415 --> 01:13:33,815
She just wanted to find our daughter.

783
01:13:33,885 --> 01:13:35,185
"Our daughter?"

784
01:13:35,185 --> 01:13:37,855
Have you heard about Geum Ba Ra?

785
01:13:38,415 --> 01:13:41,085
- Have you?
- I'm worried she's trembling somewhere.

786
01:13:41,185 --> 01:13:44,425
If they really saw her at Meeting Plaza,
then she must be with someone.

787
01:13:44,495 --> 01:13:46,765
Do you think Ba Ra ever thinks about us?

788
01:13:46,765 --> 01:13:47,865
She probably doesn't think of me.

789
01:13:48,525 --> 01:13:50,495
- You?
- Don't you dare compare me to him!

790
01:13:51,065 --> 01:13:52,065
You're so two-faced.

791
01:13:52,065 --> 01:13:53,905
Then go find your precious, pregnant Ba Ra
and live together.

792
01:13:54,005 --> 01:13:55,435
Didn't you say James's employee saw her?

793
01:13:55,965 --> 01:13:56,975
Let's just end it!

794
01:13:57,235 --> 01:13:58,275
Don't bite your nails.

795
01:13:58,275 --> 01:13:59,635
Those are my sister's nails.

796
01:14:01,875 --> 01:14:03,945
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
